---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Food Synergies"
  description="Discover powerful nutrient combinations that multiply each other's benefits — and anti-nutrient interactions to avoid."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#FFF0F3 0%,#FFF5EE 50%,#F0FBF4 100%)">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <span class="eyebrow-pill">🤝 The Synergy Effect</span>
      <h1>Food Synergies</h1>
      <p class="hero-desc">Why whole foods work better than isolated supplements — and the powerful nutrient pairs that multiply each other's benefits inside your body.</p>
      <div class="hero-note highlight-box highlight-green" style="max-width:600px;margin:1.5rem auto 0;text-align:left;">
        <strong>The key insight:</strong> Taking an isolated vitamin ignores how nutrients work in nature. In real food, nutrients co-exist with the very cofactors needed for their absorption and function. That's why a serving of salmon provides not just Vitamin D, but the fat needed to absorb it — simultaneously.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Synergy Pairs -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="eyebrow">Power Pairs</div>
        <h2>10 Nutrient Synergies You Should Know</h2>
        <p>These pairings can dramatically increase nutrient absorption and health benefits.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="synergies-grid">

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-teal)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">01</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🍊 Vitamin C</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🔴 Iron</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">↑ 67% absorption</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Vitamin C converts non-heme iron (from plants) from ferric (Fe³⁺) to ferrous (Fe²⁺) form — which your intestines can absorb far more efficiently.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Try together:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🫘 Lentils + 🫑 Bell pepper</span>
                <span>🥬 Spinach + 🍋 Lemon juice</span>
                <span>🍚 Beans + 🍅 Tomatoes</span>
                <span>🌿 Tofu + 🥦 Broccoli</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-orange)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">02</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">☀️ Vitamin D</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🦷 Calcium</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">Essential pair</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Vitamin D is required for your intestines to absorb calcium. Without adequate Vitamin D, you can drink all the milk you want and most calcium will pass through unused.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Try together:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🐟 Salmon + 🥛 Yogurt</span>
                <span>🥚 Eggs + 🧀 Cheese</span>
                <span>☀️ Sunlight + 🥛 Dairy</span>
                <span>🍄 UV mushrooms + 🌿 Tofu</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-purple)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">03</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🦴 Vitamin K2</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">☀️ Vitamin D3</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🦷 Calcium</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">Bone trio</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>D3 increases calcium absorption. K2 (specifically MK-4 and MK-7) activates proteins that direct calcium INTO bones and teeth — and AWAY from arteries where it causes calcification.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Best sources:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🟡 Natto (highest K2 on Earth)</span>
                <span>🐟 Fatty fish (D3)</span>
                <span>🧀 Hard cheese (K2 + calcium)</span>
                <span>🥚 Egg yolks (K2 + D)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-yellow)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">04</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🫒 Dietary Fat</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🔆 Fat-Soluble Vitamins (A, D, E, K)</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">Required for absorption</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Vitamins A, D, E, and K are fat-soluble — they dissolve in fat, not water. Eating them with fat is not optional; it's essential for any absorption to occur.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Try together:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🥗 Salad greens + 🫒 Olive oil</span>
                <span>🥕 Carrots + 🥑 Avocado</span>
                <span>🍠 Sweet potato + 🧈 Butter/ghee</span>
                <span>🥬 Kale + 🥜 Tahini</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-red)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">05</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">⚡ Vitamin B12</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🧬 Folate (B9)</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">DNA synthesis partners</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>B12 and Folate work together in the methylation cycle — essential for DNA synthesis and repair, cell division, and converting homocysteine (a heart disease risk marker) to safe methionine.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Try together:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🥚 Eggs + 🥬 Leafy greens</span>
                <span>🐟 Salmon + 🥦 Broccoli</span>
                <span>🧀 Dairy + 🫘 Lentils</span>
                <span>🥩 Liver (has both!)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:#06D6A0">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">06</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">😴 Magnesium</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">☀️ Vitamin D</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">Activation required</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Magnesium is needed to convert Vitamin D into its active form (calcitriol). If you're magnesium-deficient, supplementing Vitamin D may have minimal effect. Many people take D3 without fixing their magnesium first.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Try together:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🎃 Pumpkin seeds + 🍄 Mushrooms</span>
                <span>🍫 Dark chocolate + 🐟 Salmon</span>
                <span>🥬 Spinach + 🥚 Egg yolks</span>
                <span>🌰 Almonds + 🧀 Fortified foods</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-blue)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">07</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🍅 Lycopene</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🫒 Olive Oil</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">↑ 3-8x absorption</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Lycopene (the red pigment in tomatoes) is fat-soluble and dramatically increases in bioavailability when cooked with oil. Tomato sauce with olive oil provides several times more absorbable lycopene than raw tomatoes.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Best combos:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🍅 Tomato sauce + 🫒 Extra virgin olive oil</span>
                <span>🍕 Pizza (yes, genuinely healthy here!)</span>
                <span>🥗 Roasted tomatoes + EVOO drizzle</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:#F9C74F">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">08</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🟡 Curcumin (Turmeric)</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">⚫ Piperine (Black Pepper)</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">↑ 2000% absorption</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Curcumin in turmeric is poorly absorbed on its own. Piperine, the active compound in black pepper, inhibits the enzyme that breaks down curcumin — increasing its bioavailability by up to 2000%.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Classic pairings:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🍛 Curry (turmeric + black pepper)</span>
                <span>🥛 Golden milk + pinch pepper</span>
                <span>🥗 Turmeric roasted veg + black pepper</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--accent-teal)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">09</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🧅 Quercetin</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">🍵 Green Tea (EGCG)</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">Anti-inflammatory synergy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Quercetin (from onions, apples) and EGCG (from green tea) both inhibit inflammatory pathways, and together they appear to have complementary effects on reducing oxidative stress and inflammation markers.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>Pair with meals:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🧅 Red onion salad + 🍵 Green tea</span>
                <span>🍎 Apple + 🍵 Matcha latte</span>
                <span>🫑 Peppers + 🍵 Green tea with food</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="synergy-card" style="--sc:var(--primary)">
          <div class="sc-header">
            <span class="sc-num">10</span>
            <div class="sc-nutrients">
              <span class="sc-n">🥦 Sulforaphane</span>
              <span class="sc-plus">+</span>
              <span class="sc-n">⏱️ Chop &amp; Wait</span>
            </div>
            <span class="sc-boost">Enzyme activation trick</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sc-body">
            <p>Sulforaphane doesn't exist preformed in broccoli. It forms when myrosinase enzyme (released by chopping/chewing) acts on glucoraphanin. Heat destroys myrosinase — so chop, wait 5 min, THEN lightly cook.</p>
            <div class="sc-foods">
              <strong>The method:</strong>
              <div class="sc-food-list">
                <span>🥦 Chop broccoli → wait 5-10 min</span>
                <span>→ Steam lightly (not boil)</span>
                <span>🌱 Broccoli sprouts have 100x more!</span>
                <span>Add raw mustard seeds to boost further</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Anti-Nutrients -->
  <section class="section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="eyebrow">Watch Out For</div>
        <h2>Anti-Nutrient Interactions to Avoid</h2>
        <p>Some foods and habits can block nutrient absorption. Knowing these helps you time meals better.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-2">
        {[
          { emoji:'☕', title:'Coffee & Tea with Meals', issue:'Tannins in tea and coffee chelate iron and zinc, significantly reducing absorption. Can reduce iron absorption by 60-90%!', fix:'Drink coffee/tea 1+ hour before or after iron-rich meals. Especially important for vegans relying on plant iron.' },
          { emoji:'🥛', title:'Calcium Competes with Iron', issue:'High-dose calcium (from dairy or supplements) directly competes with iron for the same intestinal transporter (DMT1), reducing iron absorption by 30-50%.', fix:'Separate calcium-rich foods from iron-rich foods at different meals. Critical for women with high iron needs.' },
          { emoji:'🌾', title:'Phytates in Grains & Legumes', issue:'Phytic acid in whole grains and legumes binds iron, zinc, calcium, and magnesium — reducing their absorption significantly.', fix:'Soak, sprout, or ferment (sourdough bread!) to reduce phytates by 50-90%. Cooking helps too.' },
          { emoji:'🥬', title:'Oxalates in Spinach & Beets', issue:'Oxalic acid in spinach, beets, and almonds binds calcium, making most of the calcium in these foods unavailable. Spinach calcium is ~5% bioavailable vs. ~40% from milk.', fix:'Don\'t rely on spinach for calcium. Kale and bok choy have low oxalates and high calcium bioavailability. Boiling reduces oxalates.' },
          { emoji:'⚗️', title:'Zinc & Copper Compete', issue:'High-dose zinc supplementation depletes copper by competing for absorption. Long-term zinc supplements without copper can cause serious copper deficiency.', fix:'If supplementing zinc, also get copper from food (shellfish, dark chocolate, liver) or a balanced supplement.' },
          { emoji:'🥃', title:'Alcohol Depletes Nutrients', issue:'Alcohol is an anti-nutrient: it depletes B vitamins (especially B1, B6, B9, B12), zinc, magnesium, and vitamin C. It also impairs liver metabolism of vitamin D.', fix:'Limit alcohol, and if you drink, ensure you\'re getting plenty of these nutrients from whole foods. Avoid drinking with meals.' },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="anti-card">
            <div class="anti-header">
              <span class="anti-emoji">{item.emoji}</span>
              <h4>{item.title}</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-box highlight-red mb">
              <strong>Issue:</strong> {item.issue}
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-box highlight-green">
              <strong>Fix:</strong> {item.fix}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Summary Tips -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-sm">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="eyebrow">Key Takeaways</div>
        <h2>Practical Rules for Better Absorption</h2>
      </div>
      <div style="display:grid;gap:1rem;">
        {[
          { n:'01', t:'Always dress salads with oil', d:'Fat-soluble vitamins (A, E, K) in greens need fat. A fat-free salad dressing wastes most of the vitamins.' },
          { n:'02', t:'Squeeze lemon on beans and lentils', d:'The vitamin C in lemon juice dramatically boosts non-heme iron absorption from legumes. Make it a habit.' },
          { n:'03', t:'Always add black pepper to turmeric dishes', d:'Turmeric without pepper is nearly useless. Always combine them — it\'s baked into traditional curry recipes for a reason.' },
          { n:'04', t:'Don\'t drink tea/coffee with meals', d:'Wait at least an hour either side of iron-rich meals. Herbal teas are fine.' },
          { n:'05', t:'Soak your beans and legumes overnight', d:'Reduces phytates by ~50%, making zinc, iron, and magnesium significantly more bioavailable.' },
          { n:'06', t:'Chop broccoli first, cook it last', d:'5-10 minutes between chopping and cooking allows myrosinase to create sulforaphane. Don\'t skip this step.' },
          { n:'07', t:'Eat fermented foods regularly', d:'Fermentation reduces anti-nutrients and dramatically increases the bioavailability of minerals in the base food.' },
          { n:'08', t:'Get morning sunlight before eating', d:'Vitamin D synthesis from sunlight is most efficient in the morning. Combine with a magnesium-rich breakfast for activation.' },
        ].map(tip => (
          <div class="tip-row">
            <span class="tip-num">{tip.n}</span>
            <div>
              <strong>{tip.t}</strong>
              <p style="margin:0.15rem 0 0;font-size:0.9rem">{tip.d}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .eyebrow-pill {
    display: inline-block; background: #FFE5CC; color: #7A3800;
    padding: 0.35rem 1rem; border-radius: 50px; font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .hero-desc { font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .synergies-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
  .synergy-card {
    background: white; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    overflow: hidden; transition: all 0.2s;
    border-top: 4px solid var(--sc);
  }
  .synergy-card:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg); transform: translateY(-3px); }
  .sc-header { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-section); }
  .sc-num { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--sc); letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .sc-nutrients { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .sc-n { font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text); }
  .sc-plus { color: var(--sc); font-weight: 900; font-size: 1rem; }
  .sc-boost { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--sc); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sc) 12%, white); padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 50px; }
  .sc-body { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; }
  .sc-body p { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .sc-foods strong { font-size: 0.82rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--text-muted); display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .sc-food-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.3rem; }
  .sc-food-list span { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text); }

  .anti-card { background: white; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .anti-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .anti-emoji { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  .anti-header h4 { margin: 0; }

  .tip-row { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; align-items: flex-start; background: white; padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .tip-num { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--primary-light); line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; min-width: 2.5rem; }
  .tip-row strong { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text); }
</style>
